  "content": "### Step 4: Update existing tests to match new defaults\n\n### Step 5: Run tests to verify they pass\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-common -- --test-threads=1`\nExpected: ALL PASS\n\n\n### Step 6: Add `delete_scope` to QueryableStore trait\n\nModify `crates/corvia-kernel/src/traits.rs` — add `delete_scope` to the trait:\n\n```rust\n#[async_trait]\npub trait QueryableStore: Send + Sync {\n    async fn insert(&self, entry: &KnowledgeEntry) -> Result<()>;\n    async fn search(&self, embedding: &[f32], scope_id: &str, limit: usize) -> Result<Vec<SearchResult>>;\n    async fn get(&self, id: &uuid::Uuid) -> Result<Option<KnowledgeEntry>>;\n    async fn count(&self, scope_id: &str) -> Result<u64>;\n    async fn init_schema(&self) -> Result<()>;\n\n    /// Delete all entries in a scope. Used for test/demo teardown.\n    async fn delete_scope(&self, scope_id: &str) -> Result<()>;\n}\n```\n\nThen move `SurrealStore::delete_scope` from the inherent impl block to the trait impl block in `crates/corvia-kernel/src/knowledge_store.rs`.\n",
